Variables:
- \( x \): Number of trips using local sled dogs
- \( y \): Number of trips using trucks

Parameters:
- \( f_{sd} \): Amount of fish that can be transported per trip using local sled dogs
- \( f_{truck} \): Amount of fish that can be transported per trip using trucks
- \( c_{sd} \): Cost per trip using local sled dogs
- \( c_{truck} \): Cost per trip using trucks
- \( B \): Budget upper limit

Objective:
Maximize: \( f_{sd} \times x + f_{truck} \times y \)

Constraints:
- \( c_{sd} \times x + c_{truck} \times y \leq B \) (Budget constraint)
- \( x < y \) (Number of sled dog trips must be less than the number of truck trips)
